  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6573.53 sitting 25 points below the GEX flip at 6598, dealers are currently long gamma and providing stabilizing flow by buying this dip. The massive positive gamma wall at 6600 (19.8B) creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rally attempts, while the negative gamma floor at 6550 (-12.6B) provides a backstop where dealers flip to buying pressure. The recent GEX surge confirms dealers are heavily positioned to defend the 6550-6600 range, with particular resistance clustering around 6580-6590 levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to chop between 6550-6600 with upside capped near 6600.",
